{
  "description": "Observe your consumption analytics all in one dashboard. Analyze patterns of usage across your devices inventory.",
  "is_read_only": false,
  "layout_type": "ordered",
  "notify_list": [ ],
  "reflow_type": "fixed",
  "template_variables": [ ],
  "title": "EMnify Dashboard",
  "widgets": [
    {
      "id": 973562992734448,
      "definition": {
        "title": "About EMnify Dashboard",
        "type": "group",
        "background_color": "vivid_orange",
        "show_title": true,
        "layout_type": "ordered",
        "widgets": [
          {
            "id": 2719566117138984,
            "definition": {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://portal.emnify.com/images/main-layout-logo-dark.svg",
              "sizing": "contain",
              "margin": "md",
              "has_background": false,
              "has_border": false,
              "vertical_align": "center",
              "horizontal_align": "center"
            },
            "layout": {
              "x": 0,
              "y": 0,
              "width": 3,
              "height": 2
            }
          },
          {
            "id": 4205652380459396,
            "definition": {
              "type": "note",
              "content": "# Widgets\n\nObserve your consumption analytics all in one dashboard. Analyze usage patterns for your device inventory.\n\n# Setup\nConfigure streaming of Usage Data following the [integration guide][2],\nsections “Integration Steps” and “Verifying the integration”.\n\n# Dashboard Tuning\n\nYou can pick a period to filter the data displayed.\n\n[2]: https://www.emnify.com/integration-guides/emnify-datastreamer-integration-for-datadog",
              "background_color": "white",
              "font_size": "14",
              "text_align": "left",
              "vertical_align": "top",
              "show_tick": false,
              "tick_pos": "50%",
              "tick_edge": "left",
              "has_padding": true
            },
            "layout": {
              "x": 0,
              "y": 2,
              "width": 6,
              "height": 3
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "width": 6,
        "height": 6
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 6446661413737418,
      "definition": {
        "title": "Total Data Consumption",
        "title_size": "16",
        "title_align": "left",
        "type": "query_value",
        "requests": [
          {
            "formulas": [
              {
                "formula": "query1"
              }
            ],
            "response_format": "scalar",
            "queries": [
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume{*}.as_count()",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query1",
                "aggregator": "sum"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "autoscale": true,
        "precision": 2,
        "timeseries_background": {
          "type": "bars",
          "yaxis": {}
        }
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 6,
        "y": 0,
        "width": 6,
        "height": 6
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3360734162786772,
      "definition": {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "Use this widget to track anomalies that appear in your usage patterns.\n\nThis way you can easier troubleshoot issues in your infrastructure.",
        "background_color": "yellow",
        "font_size": "18",
        "text_align": "left",
        "vertical_align": "center",
        "show_tick": true,
        "tick_pos": "50%",
        "tick_edge": "right",
        "has_padding": true
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0,
        "width": 2,
        "height": 5,
        "is_column_break": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 406495337364450,
      "definition": {
        "title": "Total Usage with Anomalies",
        "title_size": "16",
        "title_align": "left",
        "show_legend": true,
        "legend_layout": "horizontal",
        "legend_columns": [
          "avg",
          "min",
          "max",
          "value",
          "sum"
        ],
        "type": "timeseries",
        "requests": [
          {
            "formulas": [
              {
                "alias": "Data Volume",
                "formula": "anomalies(query1, 'robust', 2)"
              }
            ],
            "response_format": "timeseries",
            "queries": [
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume{*}.as_count().rollup(sum, 3600)",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query1"
              }
            ],
            "style": {
              "palette": "green",
              "line_type": "solid",
              "line_width": "thin"
            },
            "display_type": "bars"
          }
        ],
        "yaxis": {
          "scale": "sqrt"
        }
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 2,
        "y": 0,
        "width": 10,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3392374472006114,
      "definition": {
        "title": "Devices Chunks of Total Data Consumption",
        "type": "treemap",
        "requests": [
          {
            "formulas": [
              {
                "formula": "query1"
              }
            ],
            "response_format": "scalar",
            "queries": [
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume{*} by {host}",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query1",
                "aggregator": "sum"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 5,
        "width": 10,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 6496848488480304,
      "definition": {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "See portions of total data consumption that every device takes during a selected period.",
        "background_color": "yellow",
        "font_size": "18",
        "text_align": "left",
        "vertical_align": "center",
        "show_tick": true,
        "tick_pos": "50%",
        "tick_edge": "left",
        "has_padding": true
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 10,
        "y": 5,
        "width": 2,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2374018436671430,
      "definition": {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "Daily incoming and outgoing traffic stacks show the distribution of traffic consumption among your devices during the time. ",
        "background_color": "yellow",
        "font_size": "18",
        "text_align": "left",
        "vertical_align": "center",
        "show_tick": true,
        "tick_pos": "50%",
        "tick_edge": "right",
        "has_padding": true
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 10,
        "width": 2,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 8861267507955738,
      "definition": {
        "title": "Daily Data Consumption Stacks",
        "title_size": "16",
        "title_align": "left",
        "show_legend": true,
        "legend_layout": "auto",
        "legend_columns": [
          "avg",
          "min",
          "max",
          "value",
          "sum"
        ],
        "time": {
          "live_span": "1mo"
        },
        "type": "timeseries",
        "requests": [
          {
            "formulas": [
              {
                "alias": "Data Transmitted",
                "formula": "query1"
              },
              {
                "alias": "Data Received",
                "formula": "query2"
              }
            ],
            "response_format": "timeseries",
            "queries": [
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume_tx{*} by {host}.as_count()",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query1"
              },
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume_rx{*} by {host}.as_count()",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query2"
              }
            ],
            "style": {
              "palette": "orange",
              "line_type": "solid",
              "line_width": "normal"
            },
            "display_type": "bars"
          }
        ],
        "yaxis": {
          "include_zero": false,
          "scale": "sqrt"
        }
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 2,
        "y": 10,
        "width": 10,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3084876685770464,
      "definition": {
        "title": "Monthly Data Received and Data Transmitted by host",
        "title_size": "16",
        "title_align": "left",
        "type": "scatterplot",
        "requests": {
          "table": {
            "formulas": [
              {
                "alias": "Data Transmitted",
                "dimension": "x",
                "formula": "query1"
              },
              {
                "alias": "Data Received",
                "dimension": "y",
                "formula": "duplicatedquery1"
              }
            ],
            "response_format": "scalar",
            "queries": [
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume_tx{*} by {host}.as_count()",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query1",
                "aggregator": "sum"
              },
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume_rx{*} by {host}.as_count()",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "duplicatedquery1",
                "aggregator": "sum"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "xaxis": {
          "include_zero": false,
          "scale": "log"
        },
        "yaxis": {
          "include_zero": false,
          "scale": "log"
        }
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 15,
        "width": 10,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3974593474246872,
      "definition": {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "Shows clusters of devices with similar consumption patterns.\n\nThis may help you to define the optimal pricing model.",
        "background_color": "yellow",
        "font_size": "18",
        "text_align": "left",
        "vertical_align": "center",
        "show_tick": true,
        "tick_pos": "50%",
        "tick_edge": "left",
        "has_padding": true
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 10,
        "y": 15,
        "width": 2,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 1572035223962300,
      "definition": {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "Top devices by data consumption.\n\nIn **config** you may set rules of formatting that will help you to highlight a group that has consumption that deserves attention.\n\nBy default, we highlight with red all the devices having more than *150 MB* of data consumption.",
        "background_color": "yellow",
        "font_size": "18",
        "text_align": "left",
        "vertical_align": "center",
        "show_tick": true,
        "tick_pos": "50%",
        "tick_edge": "right",
        "has_padding": true
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 20,
        "width": 2,
        "height": 5
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3157632350532354,
      "definition": {
        "title": "Top 100 devices by data usage",
        "title_size": "16",
        "title_align": "left",
        "type": "toplist",
        "requests": [
          {
            "formulas": [
              {
                "formula": "query1",
                "limit": {
                  "count": 500,
                  "order": "desc"
                }
              }
            ],
            "conditional_formats": [
              {
                "comparator": ">",
                "palette": "white_on_yellow",
                "value": 150000000
              }
            ],
            "response_format": "scalar",
            "queries": [
              {
                "query": "sum:emnify.endpoint.volume{*} by {host}.as_count()",
                "data_source": "metrics",
                "name": "query1",
                "aggregator": "sum"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "layout": {
        "x": 2,
        "y": 20,
        "width": 10,
        "height": 5
      }
    }
  ]
}
